Eventually, Cody's diligent search paid off. The light was too dim to see, but his fingertips found a hint of a line in
the wall. Tracing its path revealed the outline of a door perfectly flush with the wall to either side. "Too easy,"
Cody remarked in satisfaction. He then winced. "I didn't mean that," he muttered, hoping no malign deity was listening
that might decide to puncture his confidence.
